invokeSetOptions

public void invokeSetOptions(java.lang.String optionListString)
Set MetaMap server options. This method sends preprocessed options to MetaMap server. The parameter optionListString is in the form of: 
   "[" + "'" + option + "'" + "," + + "'" + option + "'" + ... "]"
E.G.: 
    optionListString = "['-y','-D','-i']";
or: 
    optionListString = "['-yDi']";
sets options -y -D and -i.

Specified by:
invokeSetOptions in interface MetaMapApi
Parameters:
optionListString - a string of MetaMap options
